==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: differentia
<hw>dif`fer*en"ti*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Differenti⟦ae⟧</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L. See
<er>Difference</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Logic)</fld> <def>The
formal or distinguishing part of the essence of a species, by which it
is distinguished from other members of its genus; the characteristic
attribute of a species; specific difference; <as>as, a proper definition
must have both genus and <ex>differentia</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>the set of characteristics distinguishing an entity
from related entities.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>differentiable</ent>⟦br⟧
